        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         If it's still unclear Angier, I'll sum up the pro-hp argument with two points:</P><P><b>One:</b> HPs are the only "stat" which doesn't have a point of dimishing returns.  Adding more hps always provides a benefit, and in the same ratio no matter how many you have.</P><P><b>Two:</b> I'll quote Savan:<BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>A few people have touched on this factor and it primarily has to do with greatly enhanced flexibility in all aspects of the game -- raid, group and solo...<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote>HP gear is universal, not situational.  You'll use it in all phases of the game because it provides a constant benefit.  Situatiionally yes, there will be times when you wear gear other than hp gear, but generally speaking you'll get more use from hp gear.</P><P></P><P>--Nergal Teir'Draconis, Knights of Twilight (Tunare)<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
