         When pulling (Especially lately where more than 4 mobs can be bashing/smacking/casting on you at once) I've had a number of times where I tried to cast Death Peace (1 second cast time and it hasn't given me the "You fall to the ground" message YET!) and it's been interrupted or a spell has landed on me after I feigned.</P><P>I've had to recast as many as four times before I got it to work and been at 24 hps on one occasion. HPs saved me.</P><P>When I'm at 60% mana and waiting for a pull or pulling I can afford to keep lich up and get to FOM and losse 2 bubs of health and still feel safe with only 3 bubs of health. Pulls don't always bring mobs in the second the first one dies, so it's important to be able to keep lich going and still have a good HP buffer.</P><P>When Soloing, before I had a modest ammount of hit points if I got two or three adds and I was fighting, keeping all the mobs snared/feared, dotting the one my pet was on and generaly blasting mana away like it was going out of style. </P><P>This will usually happen right when the named mob I've been camping for 6 hours spawns.. I'll be at 60% mana anyway, I'll snare/fear/dot whatever and send pet, then my HP buffs will fade, SoW wears off and two adds will just HAPPEN to roam over my camp spot for the first time in 6 hours.</P><P>I can A: Gate and lose the named to whatever druid is hanging around in the zone eagerly waiting to be the bane of my existance. Or I can B: Suck it up, dig my heels in and get evil on this stuff.</P><P>So if you remember right, I'm at 60% mana, I lose 2 bubs of health from the mobs beating on me before I get them mezzed/snared/feared/rooted. My Aego fades and I lose an instan 1k hps. My SoW wears off so I HAVE to keep them all snared. I'm still liching, but only at 3 bubs of health, I get down to 1 bub of mana while tossing the spells I need to at the named and the two adds.</P><P>Once things are under control, I can sit and continue dropping health for mana.. I'm down to 2 bubs (But with a LOT of hit points I'm still well over 1k).. one add breaks fear and comes and whacks me.. I spend another 300 hps and the half bub of mana I regenned getting him back under control. I then toss a Vexing at the named to get him hurt faster and get some of my health back.. but now I'm at 1/2 bub of mana but still liching.</P><P>I sit and continue to lose health for mana. In the end.. I'm able to keep regenerating mana even with only 2 bubs of health because I'm not at a criticaly low health level.</P><P>In the end.. I win based soley on my ability to keep the mana machine going. Longer than I would have been able to if I didn't have it.</P><P>I've had this type of thing happen more than once and I sometimes think Verant had a "Bad luck" modifier in the random number generator.</P><P>That's what it means to me.</P><P><BR><img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
